set @max_date:= (select max(flow_start_time) from api_ingestion_metastore where status in ('success','user_entry'));set @new_api_start_time:= (select case when api_start_time is null or api_start_time='' then api_start_time when api_end_time is null or api_end_time='' then case when flow_start_time >= delta_date then delta_date else flow_start_time end when flow_start_time >= api_end_time and flow_start_time >= delta_date then case when api_end_time>=delta_date then delta_date else api_end_time end when api_end_time >= flow_start_time and api_end_time >= delta_date then case when flow_start_time>=delta_date then delta_date else flow_start_time end when delta_date >= api_end_time and delta_date >= flow_start_time then case when api_end_time>=flow_start_time then flow_start_time else api_end_time end else flow_start_time end as new_api_start_date from api_ingestion_metastore where flow_start_time=@max_date);set @new_api_end_time:= (select case when api_end_time is null or api_end_time = '' then api_end_time else now() end from api_ingestion_metastore where flow_start_time=@max_date);

Adding user input to flow file attribute
All the files will be fetched from SFTP server to nifi's cluster. Calculation of total number of records fetched , total file size will happen in this processor group .
Wait for all the files to be placed on s3
once all the files is put on s3 , then the flow end time will be recorded in ingestion metadata table
Clearing the information of total number of records fetched , total file size of last workflow run from nifi's local state
If all the fetched flow files is not put on s3 , then a failure status will be inserted in ingestion meta data table

once all the fetched flow files is put in s3 then a success job status will be inserted in ingestion metadata table . Also if table name is provided by user glue crawler will run . Upon completion, the crawler creates or updates one or more tables in your Data Catalog

Performs a listing of the files residing on an SFTP server. For each file that is found on the remote server, a new FlowFile will be created with the filename attribute set to the name of the file on the remote server. After performing a listing of files, the timestamp of the newest file is stored. This allows the Processor to list only files that have been added or modified after this date the next time that the Processor is run.
Updating job status to "IN PROGRESS" & Storing timestamp of the last file fetched from the SFTP server
Fetching timestamp of the last file fetched from the SFTP server from ingestion metadata table

MANDATORY FIELDS
1.Data source 2.Table name(in case user wants to run crawler)
NOTE : Only one table will be created either for csv files or tsv files
Only those files will be fetched from the SFTP server , as per the user's file filter regex
